snippet.title: Surface Area and Volume of a Sphere | MathHelp.com
snippet.description:
Need a custom math course? Visit http://www.MathHelp.com.

This lesson covers surface area and volume of a sphere. Students learn the formulas for the area and volume of spheres, and are asked to solve problems using these formulas. The word problems in this lesson involve spheres that are melted down and recast as cones or cylinders, the amount of paint needed to cover a hemisphere (half of a sphere), and so on.
